---
// request-path-strip — Chapter 074 Lesson 1, "Two layers: edge WAF and
// application limiter", section "The two layers: edge controls and application
// controls".
//
// The reusable spine of the chapter. One request's lifecycle laid out
// left-to-right, with the two rate-limiting rings drawn as nested boxes so the
// SPATIAL nesting carries the lesson:
//
//   Client → ┌ Edge / WAF ring ┐ → ┌ Vercel Function ──────────────┐ →
//            └ sees IP, path…  ┘   │  { App limiter ring: +email…}  │
//                                  └ Server Action / route handler ┘
//            → Better Auth verify → Database
//
// The edge ring is its OWN box, OUTSIDE the function. The app limiter ring is a
// box NESTED INSIDE the function box. That outside/inside contrast is the whole
// point — the edge sees only IP/path/headers (no body), the app ring runs after
// parsing where the email/user/org are finally visible.
//
// Why plain HTML+CSS, not <ArrowDiagram>: the nested "ring inside the function"
// is native here (a div inside a div, devtools-inspectable), whereas ArrowDiagram
// is a flat box model and its LeaderLine arrows can't span a parent→child nesting
// cleanly. Same palette + "fieldset legend" pill-label discipline as the sibling
// TwoAttackContrast figure so the chapter reads as one consistent map.
//
// Palette pinned to a light color-scheme so the hand-picked tints survive dark
// mode; margin:0 resets defeat Starlight's injected prose margins; `not-content`
// opts the figure body out of prose styling.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';

const sans = "system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif";
const mono = 'ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace';

const INK = '#1e293b'; // slate-800 — primary ink
const INK_SOFT = '#64748b'; // slate-500 — muted text
const INK_FAINT = '#94a3b8'; // slate-400 — labels / dimmed
const SURFACE = '#ffffff';
const GRID = '#e2e8f0'; // slate-200 — soft borders
const CARD_BG = 'var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar)'; // what the pill labels paint over

const EDGE = '#7c3aed'; // violet-600 — the edge / WAF ring
const APP = '#0d9488'; // teal-600 — the application ring

const ALT =
	'One request travels left to right: Client, then through the edge / WAF ring (which sees IP, path and headers, and blocks before any compute is billed), then into the Vercel Function running the Server Action or route handler. Nested inside that function box is the application limiter ring, which additionally sees the email, user, org and body. The request then reaches Better Auth verify and finally the Database.';
---

<Figure
	caption="Two rings on one request path. The edge ring runs before your function and sees only IP, path, and headers. The application ring runs inside the function, after parsing, where the email and the user are finally visible."
>
	<div class="rps not-content" role="img" aria-label={ALT}>
		{/* ── Client ── */}
		<div class="rps-node rps-plain">
			<span class="rps-role">Browser</span>
			<span class="rps-name">Client</span>
		</div>

		<div class="rps-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 40 14" preserveAspectRatio="none">
				<line x1="0" y1="7" x2="34" y2="7" stroke={INK_FAINT} stroke-width="2"></line>
				<polygon points="40,7 31,3 31,11" fill={INK_FAINT}></polygon>
			</svg>
		</div>

		{/* ── Edge / WAF ring — its own box, OUTSIDE the function ── */}
		<div class="rps-ring rps-ring-edge">
			<span class="rps-legend rps-legend-edge">Edge / WAF ring</span>
			<span class="rps-ring-sees">sees IP, path, headers</span>
			<span class="rps-ring-note">blocks before compute is billed</span>
		</div>

		<div class="rps-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 40 14" preserveAspectRatio="none">
				<line x1="0" y1="7" x2="34" y2="7" stroke={INK_FAINT} stroke-width="2"></line>
				<polygon points="40,7 31,3 31,11" fill={INK_FAINT}></polygon>
			</svg>
		</div>

		{/* ── Vercel Function box, with the app limiter ring NESTED inside ── */}
		<div class="rps-fn">
			<span class="rps-legend rps-legend-fn">Vercel Function</span>
			<span class="rps-fn-sub">Server Action / route handler</span>

			<div class="rps-ring rps-ring-app">
				<span class="rps-legend rps-legend-app">App limiter ring</span>
				<span class="rps-ring-sees rps-ring-sees-app">
					<strong>+ email, user, org, body</strong>
				</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="rps-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 40 14" preserveAspectRatio="none">
				<line x1="0" y1="7" x2="34" y2="7" stroke={INK_FAINT} stroke-width="2"></line>
				<polygon points="40,7 31,3 31,11" fill={INK_FAINT}></polygon>
			</svg>
		</div>

		{/* ── Better Auth verify ── */}
		<div class="rps-node rps-plain">
			<span class="rps-role">Auth</span>
			<span class="rps-name">Better Auth</span>
			<span class="rps-node-sub">verify</span>
		</div>

		<div class="rps-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 40 14" preserveAspectRatio="none">
				<line x1="0" y1="7" x2="34" y2="7" stroke={INK_FAINT} stroke-width="2"></line>
				<polygon points="40,7 31,3 31,11" fill={INK_FAINT}></polygon>
			</svg>
		</div>

		{/* ── Database ── */}
		<div class="rps-node rps-db">
			<span class="rps-role">Store</span>
			<span class="rps-name">Database</span>
		</div>
	</div>
</Figure>

<style define:vars={{ INK, INK_SOFT, INK_FAINT, SURFACE, GRID, CARD_BG, EDGE, APP, sans, mono }}>
	.rps {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: nowrap;
		align-items: stretch;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 0;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 26px 2px 12px;
		color-scheme: light;
		font-family: var(--sans);
		color: var(--INK);
	}

	.rps :global(*) {
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* ── plain nodes: Client, Better Auth, Database ── */
	.rps-node {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 3px;
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding: 12px 12px;
		border: 1.5px solid var(--GRID);
		border-radius: 11px;
		background: var(--SURFACE);
		text-align: center;
		min-width: 84px;
	}
	.rps-db {
		border-radius: 11px / 22px;
	}

	.rps-role {
		font-size: 9px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--INK-FAINT);
		line-height: 1.2;
	}
	.rps-name {
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 800;
		line-height: 1.15;
		color: var(--INK);
	}
	.rps-node-sub {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 9.5px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--INK-SOFT);
		line-height: 1.2;
	}

	/* ── a ring box (edge, and the nested app ring) ── */
	.rps-ring {
		position: relative;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 4px;
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding: 16px 14px 13px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.rps-ring-edge {
		border: 2px dashed var(--EDGE);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--EDGE) 7%, var(--SURFACE));
		min-width: 132px;
	}
	.rps-ring-app {
		border: 2px dashed var(--APP);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--APP) 10%, var(--SURFACE));
		min-width: 138px;
		margin-top: 8px; /* clear the function's own legend pill */
	}

	.rps-ring-sees {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 10px;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.3;
		color: var(--INK);
		max-width: 16ch;
	}
	.rps-ring-sees-app strong {
		color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--APP) 35%, var(--INK));
	}
	.rps-ring-note {
		font-size: 9px;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.25;
		color: var(--INK-SOFT);
		max-width: 17ch;
	}

	/* ── the Vercel Function box that WRAPS the app ring ── */
	.rps-fn {
		position: relative;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 4px;
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding: 16px 14px 14px;
		border: 1.5px solid var(--INK-FAINT);
		border-radius: 13px;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--GRID) 35%, var(--SURFACE));
	}
	.rps-fn-sub {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 9px;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--INK-SOFT);
	}

	/* ── "fieldset legend" pills straddling each box's top border ── */
	.rps-legend {
		display: block;
		width: fit-content;
		align-self: center;
		padding: 1px 8px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-size: 9.5px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		line-height: 1.5;
		white-space: nowrap;
		background: var(--CARD-BG);
	}
	/* lift each pill onto its parent's top border line */
	.rps-legend-edge {
		margin-top: -25px; /* pill half-height + ring padding-top + border */
		color: var(--EDGE);
		border: 1.5px solid var(--EDGE);
	}
	.rps-legend-fn {
		margin-top: -25px;
		color: var(--INK-SOFT);
		border: 1.5px solid var(--INK-FAINT);
	}
	.rps-legend-app {
		margin-top: -24px;
		color: var(--APP);
		border: 1.5px solid var(--APP);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--APP) 10%, var(--SURFACE));
	}

	/* ── arrows between segments ── */
	.rps-arrow {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		align-self: center;
		width: 34px;
		padding: 0 3px;
	}
	.rps-arrow svg {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		height: 14px;
		overflow: visible;
	}

	/* ── narrower viewports: trim the segments so the strip stays one line ── */
	@media (max-width: 860px) {
		.rps-node {
			min-width: 74px;
			padding: 11px 9px;
		}
		.rps-ring-edge,
		.rps-ring-app {
			min-width: 116px;
		}
		.rps-arrow {
			width: 24px;
		}
		.rps-name {
			font-size: 13px;
		}
	}

	/* ── phones: a 5-segment horizontal strip can't fit ~300px; let it scroll as
	      one intact swipeable line rather than crushing the boxes. ── */
	@media (max-width: 620px) {
		.rps {
			justify-content: flex-start;
			overflow-x: auto;
			padding-bottom: 8px;
			-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
			scrollbar-width: thin;
		}
		.rps-node,
		.rps-ring,
		.rps-fn,
		.rps-arrow {
			flex: 0 0 auto;
		}
	}
</style>
